updateViewState

protected void updateViewState()
Many views include components such as lists, tables, etc. Often, these components need to be updated if a state changes. This method can instruct the view to save update itself. The view itself has to know what to do.

The default implementation ignores the request.

You do not need to call super.updateViewState() when overriding this method.

Overrides:
updateViewState in class EodispView

handlePopup

updateRegistrations

public void updateRegistrations()
This is used to update the enable state of actions registered by the implementing component.

New components should not be added here, but always with the ActionSourceProvider.registerActions() method.

For actions that should be added/removed to the menus at runtime, implement the DynamicActionSourceProvider interface.

Specified by:
updateRegistrations in interface ActionSourceProvider
